// This program is a gym database management system that allows users to manage classes, trainers, equipment, members, and class registrations. 
// The system provides functionality to browse, add, edit, and delete records in each of the tables. 
// The user interface is built using Handlebars templates, which display the records in a table format with appropriate buttons for each action.
// The "Delete" button includes a confirmation prompt to prevent accidental deletions. 
// The "Add New" and "Edit" buttons link to forms for adding new records or editing existing ones. 
// The "Reset Dababase" button allows users to reset the database to its initial state, which is useful for testing and development purposes.
// The program is run by running "npm install" to install the necessary dependencies, and then "npm start" to start the server.
// The server runs on port 1342, and the user can access the application by navigating to "http://localhost:1342" in their web browser.

